article.description: Adam Grant had 17 points as Bryant beat Niagara 73-62 on Monday night.
article.headline: Grant scores 17 to carry Bryant past Niagara 73-62
article.linkText: Grant scores 17 to carry Bryant past Niagara 73-62
article.story: NIAGARA, N.Y. -- Adam Grant had 17 points as Bryant beat Niagara 73-62 on Monday night. Benson Lin had 10 points and eight rebounds for Bryant (4-2), which won its fourth straight game. Charles Pride added 10 points. Hall Elisias had seven rebounds for the visitors. James Towns had 21 points and eight rebounds for the Purple Eagles who have now lost four consecutive games to start the season. Raheem Solomon added 16 points. Greg Kuakumensah had 10 points and 10 rebounds. Bryant faces Drexel on the road on Wednesday. Niagara looks for its first win of the season against Purdue Fort Wayne on the road next Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
